WEBVTT

00:02.915 --> 00:04.482
- ♪ Hey, here comes Sunny
keeping it fun ♪

00:04.613 --> 00:06.223
♪ Never says never,
never gives up ♪

00:06.354 --> 00:08.399
♪ It's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:08.530 --> 00:10.097
♪ Hey

00:10.227 --> 00:11.924
♪ Gear up and go
in the Glam Van ♪

00:12.055 --> 00:13.665
♪ Hair styling
with her best friends ♪

00:13.796 --> 00:15.972
♪ It's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:16.103 --> 00:19.280
♪ Oh, it's a Sunny Day

00:19.410 --> 00:21.586
♪ She'll put a smile
on your face ♪

00:21.717 --> 00:23.327
- Whoo-hoo!

00:23.458 --> 00:27.984
- ♪ Sunny is shining
all the way ♪

00:28.115 --> 00:31.379
♪ Yeah, she's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:31.509 --> 00:33.772
♪ Having a sunny, sunny day

00:33.903 --> 00:35.078
- Hoo-hoo!

00:39.952 --> 00:41.998
[mellow music]

00:42.129 --> 00:43.608
- [yawns]

00:43.739 --> 00:46.133
♪

00:46.263 --> 00:48.222
- Maybe if I did this hairstyle

00:48.352 --> 00:50.485
I wonder how it would
look upside down.

00:50.615 --> 00:52.008
- [grunts,
giggles]

00:52.139 --> 00:53.531
Looks the same to me.

00:53.662 --> 00:55.403
- Wow,

00:55.533 --> 00:57.492
coming up with a new
hairstyle is tough work.

00:57.622 --> 01:00.060
- Ah, flowers fresh
from our roof garden.

01:00.190 --> 01:02.192
Nature always inspires me.

01:02.323 --> 01:03.498
- Huh.

01:03.628 --> 01:05.326
A new hair inspired by nature:

01:05.456 --> 01:06.892
that's a great idea.

01:07.023 --> 01:09.417
- Rox, you do know
you're upside down?

01:09.547 --> 01:11.027
- Uh-huh,
I think better this way.

01:11.158 --> 01:12.507
- [gasps]
I've got it.

01:12.637 --> 01:14.509
If we wanna be
inspired by nature,

01:14.639 --> 01:16.859
there's only
one place to look:

01:16.989 --> 01:18.208
the great outdoors.

01:18.339 --> 01:21.037
- Oh, we could go on a picnic.
Or hiking?

01:21.168 --> 01:22.169
- What about a camping trip?

01:22.299 --> 01:24.214
- Camping? Ya-hoo!

01:24.345 --> 01:25.868
- I've never been
camping before.

01:25.998 --> 01:28.436
It sounds fun! Let's do it.

01:28.566 --> 01:29.437
- Great.

01:29.567 --> 01:32.657
♪

01:32.788 --> 01:34.181
Tent--check.

01:34.311 --> 01:35.965
Blankets...

01:36.096 --> 01:38.098
[grunts]

01:38.228 --> 01:39.664
Um, Doodle?

01:39.795 --> 01:42.363
- [yawns]
Sorry, Sunny.

01:42.493 --> 01:44.495
Just keeping everything
warm for you.

01:44.626 --> 01:48.282
And snuggly and oh-so-comfy.

01:48.412 --> 01:50.371
[yawns]
Just five more minutes.

01:50.501 --> 01:52.851
- Sorry, Doodle,
gotta pack this too.

01:52.982 --> 01:54.940
- [chuckles]Or not.

01:55.071 --> 01:56.986
♪

01:57.117 --> 01:58.422
- Thanks, Doodle.

01:58.553 --> 02:00.816
I'm leaving you
in charge of the salon.

02:00.946 --> 02:02.557
- [yawning]

02:02.687 --> 02:04.559
Luckily,
my bed is the perfect place

02:04.689 --> 02:06.038
to keep an eye on things.

02:06.169 --> 02:07.344
[snores]

02:07.475 --> 02:09.085
- Uh, hey, Sunny?

02:09.216 --> 02:12.001
How many marshmallows
is too many marshmallows?

02:12.132 --> 02:13.568
- I'm not sure,

02:13.698 --> 02:15.657
but I think that's
probably enough.

02:15.787 --> 02:17.398
- [humming]

02:17.528 --> 02:20.227
I'll take one of these,
ooh, my feather duster--

02:20.357 --> 02:21.532
can't forget that.

02:21.663 --> 02:22.881
And definitely some glitter.

02:23.012 --> 02:25.232
- [grunts]
All packed.

02:25.362 --> 02:28.844
Oh, Blair, could you grab my
compass on your way out please?

02:28.974 --> 02:30.367
- Definitely.

02:30.498 --> 02:32.282
Can't forget this.

02:32.413 --> 02:35.067
Uh, what is it exactly?

02:35.198 --> 02:36.852
- You see the little dial?

02:36.982 --> 02:38.027
It points north.

02:38.158 --> 02:39.202
When you have a compass,

02:39.333 --> 02:40.769
you can always
find your way home.

02:40.899 --> 02:43.989
I never go camping without one.

02:44.120 --> 02:45.469
[store bell jingles]

02:45.600 --> 02:47.558
- Compass--check.

02:47.689 --> 02:49.343
♪

02:49.473 --> 02:52.389
[grunting]

02:52.520 --> 02:55.827
Ooh, my new copy
of "Manicure Monthly."

02:55.958 --> 02:57.307
I might need it.

02:57.438 --> 03:00.658
You can never be too prepared.

03:00.789 --> 03:03.705
[grunting]

03:03.835 --> 03:05.185
[upbeat music]

03:05.315 --> 03:07.622
- I can't wait to go.
Let's go!

03:07.752 --> 03:09.319
Um, why aren't we going?

03:09.450 --> 03:11.887
- I'm sure Blair
will be here any minute.

03:12.017 --> 03:12.670
Oh, here she is.

03:12.801 --> 03:14.237
And--whoa.

03:14.368 --> 03:16.021
- Here, let us help.

03:16.152 --> 03:18.633
[grunting]

03:18.763 --> 03:20.504
- [giggling]
Did you leave

03:20.635 --> 03:22.506
anything in the salon?

03:22.637 --> 03:25.117
- [laughs]
What's the point of going away

03:25.248 --> 03:27.555
if you're going
to take everything with you?

03:27.685 --> 03:30.035
A feather duster? Glitter?

03:30.166 --> 03:33.256
The latest issue
of "Manicure Monthly"?

03:33.387 --> 03:35.171
- I like to be prepared.

03:35.302 --> 03:37.565
- Well, if that's everything,

03:37.695 --> 03:40.350
and I think that is everything.
[laughter]

03:40.481 --> 03:42.831
- Ready, set...

03:42.961 --> 03:46.356
[together]
Gear up and go!

03:46.487 --> 03:48.619
- Buckle up and let's go.

03:48.750 --> 03:51.318
♪

03:51.448 --> 03:54.321
[engine roars]

03:54.451 --> 04:01.502
♪

04:04.766 --> 04:07.812
- Oh, it's so pretty!

04:07.943 --> 04:09.945
You'll definitely
find inspiration here

04:10.075 --> 04:12.077
for new hairstyles.

04:12.208 --> 04:13.078
[laughing]

04:13.209 --> 04:15.298
- Blair, wait up!

04:15.429 --> 04:17.257
- Hey, don't forget your stuff!

04:17.387 --> 04:20.521
Guess she's really
excited to go camping.

04:20.651 --> 04:23.611
- Wow, this is amazing.

04:23.741 --> 04:26.266
[grunting
Sighing]

04:26.396 --> 04:27.441
- Here we are.

04:27.571 --> 04:29.791
- Home sweet home.

04:29.921 --> 04:32.794
[mellow music]

04:32.924 --> 04:34.230
♪

04:34.361 --> 04:37.015
Hm--eww.

04:37.146 --> 04:40.715
A little dusting here.

04:40.845 --> 04:43.370
Oh, this should be comfy.

04:43.500 --> 04:45.502
♪

04:45.633 --> 04:48.113
[sighing]

04:48.244 --> 04:50.072
- Um, Blair?

04:50.202 --> 04:53.380
There's no time to read
about new nail color just yet.

04:53.510 --> 04:54.772
- Rox is right.

04:54.903 --> 04:56.252
We should set up camp.

04:56.383 --> 04:58.950
This is where
the fun really starts.

04:59.081 --> 05:02.563
[all grunting]

05:02.693 --> 05:03.694
- I've got it!

05:03.825 --> 05:05.479
I've got it--ohh!

05:05.609 --> 05:07.916
I don't got it.

05:08.046 --> 05:09.309
- [giggles]

05:09.439 --> 05:11.223
♪

05:11.354 --> 05:13.225
- I've got water!

05:13.356 --> 05:17.099
[water sloshing]

05:17.229 --> 05:18.927
[sighs]
Huh?

05:19.057 --> 05:20.624
Empty?

05:20.755 --> 05:23.453
They were definitely
full a moment ago.

05:23.584 --> 05:25.412
- It's okay, Blair.

05:25.542 --> 05:27.109
This should be enough firewood.

05:27.239 --> 05:29.111
♪

05:29.241 --> 05:30.939
- [yelps]

05:31.069 --> 05:34.943
Camping is really hard work.

05:35.073 --> 05:35.987
[screaming]

05:36.118 --> 05:37.641
- What's up, Blair?

05:37.772 --> 05:39.339
- It's what's down
that's the problem.

05:39.469 --> 05:41.645
A bug!
[squeals]

05:41.776 --> 05:43.734
- Oh, it's so cute!
Aren't you?

05:43.865 --> 05:46.084
[baby talk]
So cute and teeny-weeny!

05:46.215 --> 05:48.870
- I'm not sure
I'm very good at camping.

05:49.000 --> 05:52.003
I've chipped my nail polish,
spilled some glitter,

05:52.134 --> 05:54.702
I've got a twig in my hair
and mud on my dress

05:54.832 --> 05:57.922
and why are there
so many bugs everywhere!

05:58.053 --> 05:59.837
- Oh, don't worry, Blair.

05:59.968 --> 06:01.709
There's lots
to love about nature

06:01.839 --> 06:02.971
if you know where to look.

06:03.101 --> 06:07.062
[western music]

06:07.192 --> 06:10.282
♪ The next time that you're
wondering where I'm off to ♪

06:10.413 --> 06:13.373
♪ I'll say the wild
was calling out to me ♪

06:13.503 --> 06:15.331
- ♪ Ooh-ooh

06:15.462 --> 06:17.638
- ♪ And once you know the
great outdoors like I do ♪

06:17.768 --> 06:19.509
- Oh, yeah!

06:19.640 --> 06:21.903
- ♪ You'll never wonder
where I'm gonna be ♪

06:22.033 --> 06:23.861
- ♪ So don't look for me
at the movies ♪

06:23.992 --> 06:25.950
- ♪ Don't look for me
at the mall ♪

06:26.081 --> 06:28.039
♪ If you don't
see the open sky ♪

06:28.170 --> 06:30.085
both:
♪ Don't look for me at all

06:30.215 --> 06:31.521
♪ Outside, outside

06:31.652 --> 06:33.610
♪ I'm gonna be outside

06:33.741 --> 06:35.351
♪ Outside, outside

06:35.482 --> 06:37.875
♪ I'm gonna be outside

06:38.006 --> 06:40.269
- ♪ If you think nature
should be celebrated ♪

06:40.400 --> 06:42.227
- ♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah

06:42.358 --> 06:45.448
- ♪ Where birds and trees
and flowers can be found ♪

06:45.579 --> 06:48.538
- ♪ If you think
staying clean is overrated ♪

06:48.669 --> 06:50.148
- ♪ Oh, yeah
both: ♪ Then pack a bag

06:50.279 --> 06:51.323
♪ Come on!
We're nature-bound ♪

06:51.454 --> 06:53.108
- Yeah!
- [laughs]

06:53.238 --> 06:54.675
both: ♪ So don't look for us
at the movies ♪

06:54.805 --> 06:56.894
♪ Don't look for us
at the mall ♪

06:57.025 --> 06:58.766
♪ If you don't see
the open sky ♪

06:58.896 --> 07:00.463
♪ Don't look for us at all

07:00.594 --> 07:02.378
♪ Outside, outside

07:02.509 --> 07:04.119
♪ We're gonna be outside

07:04.249 --> 07:06.382
♪ Outside, outside

07:06.513 --> 07:07.731
♪ We're gonna be outside

07:07.862 --> 07:08.993
- Whoo!
- [giggling]

07:09.124 --> 07:11.300
See? Lots to love.

07:11.431 --> 07:12.301
- Especially spiders.

07:12.432 --> 07:13.998
Honestly, Blair,

07:14.129 --> 07:16.784
they're great
when you get to know them.

07:16.914 --> 07:19.482
- Sure,
with their pokey-out eyes

07:19.613 --> 07:21.658
and all those wiggling legs.

07:21.789 --> 07:23.878
They're really great.

07:24.008 --> 07:25.836
- That's it!
Thanks, Blair!

07:25.967 --> 07:27.708
You've just given me an idea

07:27.838 --> 07:29.187
for what my latest
hairstyle could be.

07:29.318 --> 07:30.711
- I have?

07:30.841 --> 07:32.408
You're welcome.

07:32.539 --> 07:34.454
- And I think it might be
the perfect hairstyle

07:34.584 --> 07:36.368
to try on Rox.

07:36.499 --> 07:37.761
Now, where's my hairspray?

07:37.892 --> 07:39.110
- I put it in the tent.

07:39.241 --> 07:40.198
- Then let's go.

07:40.329 --> 07:41.591
- Will you be okay, Blair?

07:41.722 --> 07:43.201
- I'll be fine.

07:43.332 --> 07:45.203
Just sitting here,
not worrying about bugs.

07:45.334 --> 07:46.727
[nervous breathing]

07:46.857 --> 07:49.120
Good luck with
the new hairstyle.

07:49.251 --> 07:50.992
- Let's get to work.

07:51.122 --> 07:53.081
- You're gonna love this style,
Rox.

07:53.211 --> 07:55.257
- I can't wait!
[giggles]

07:55.387 --> 07:58.216
[upbeat music]

07:58.347 --> 07:59.914
♪

08:00.044 --> 08:02.438
- Now that I've got all
the ponytails divided...

08:02.569 --> 08:05.136
- Are you sticking a pipe
cleaner in my hair?

08:05.267 --> 08:07.530
- Yup!
It's a trick of the trade.

08:07.661 --> 08:09.793
Just wait and see.

08:09.924 --> 08:11.969
Flip flop over the top.

08:12.100 --> 08:19.194
♪

08:22.197 --> 08:25.417
- Bend like so, and voilà!

08:25.548 --> 08:26.984
- Wow, Sunny!

08:27.115 --> 08:28.508
[gasps]
I love it!

08:28.638 --> 08:30.858
- Check this out.

08:30.988 --> 08:31.946
- Look at me!

08:32.076 --> 08:33.991
I'm a walking spider!

08:34.122 --> 08:35.166
[giggling]

08:35.297 --> 08:36.646
- [giggles]

08:36.777 --> 08:38.343
And now for
the finishing touches

08:38.474 --> 08:40.868
and then we'll
go and show Blair.

08:40.998 --> 08:43.871
[light music]

08:44.001 --> 08:46.569
- I can love
the great outdoors.

08:46.700 --> 08:50.878
Just reading my magazine
while relaxing in nature.

08:51.008 --> 08:53.228
I can do this.

08:53.358 --> 08:54.621
No, I can't do this.

08:54.751 --> 08:56.840
No, I can't do this.
I wanna go home!

08:56.971 --> 09:00.322
Oh, if I see one more spider,
I'll scream.

09:00.452 --> 09:01.628
[gasp]

09:01.758 --> 09:06.720
[stammering]
Giant spider!

09:08.983 --> 09:10.201
[both giggling]

09:10.332 --> 09:10.941
- [screaming]
- What was that?

09:11.072 --> 09:12.508
- That sounded like Blair.

09:12.639 --> 09:14.597
But where is she?

09:14.728 --> 09:15.772
[gasp]

09:15.903 --> 09:18.514
Maybe Blair saw Rox's hair

09:18.645 --> 09:22.170
looking like a giant spider.

09:22.300 --> 09:27.392
- Uh, Sunny?

09:27.523 --> 09:29.003
What are we looking for?

09:29.133 --> 09:32.223
- I think Blaire saw
your shadow in the tent

09:32.354 --> 09:35.792
and thought your hair
was a real spider.

09:35.923 --> 09:37.838
And now she's gone.

09:37.968 --> 09:39.883
- This isn't good.

09:40.014 --> 09:41.537
Blair!

09:41.668 --> 09:43.234
Where are you?

09:43.365 --> 09:44.801
- Blair? Blair?

09:44.932 --> 09:47.151
Blair? You can come out now.

09:47.282 --> 09:48.457
It's just my hair.

09:48.588 --> 09:50.372
No spiders here.

09:50.502 --> 09:51.591
Ugh, it's official.

09:51.721 --> 09:54.115
Blair has left the campsite.

09:54.245 --> 09:57.161
- She must've been really
scared if she ran away.

09:57.292 --> 09:59.381
But now she could be anywhere.

09:59.511 --> 10:01.905
- Why did my hair
have to be so awesome?

10:02.036 --> 10:03.646
Why?

10:03.777 --> 10:05.169
- Well,
we're going to find her.

10:05.300 --> 10:06.170
- But how?

10:06.301 --> 10:07.781
These woods are huge,

10:07.911 --> 10:10.740
and Blair's pretty small.

10:10.871 --> 10:11.872
- [gasps]

10:12.002 --> 10:13.047
That's Blair's glitter!

10:13.177 --> 10:14.701
I think she went that way.

10:14.831 --> 10:16.441
Come on!

10:16.572 --> 10:18.618
♪

10:18.748 --> 10:21.403
- Blair? Blair?
Where are you?

10:21.533 --> 10:22.752
- [gasps]
Look!

10:22.883 --> 10:23.884
More glitter!

10:24.014 --> 10:25.668
That's a clue she was here.

10:25.799 --> 10:27.583
But which way did she go next?

10:27.714 --> 10:29.585
- Hey, there she is!

10:29.716 --> 10:32.240
Blair,
you had us really worried.

10:32.370 --> 10:33.589
Oh.

10:33.720 --> 10:35.112
Sorry, Sunny.

10:35.243 --> 10:37.288
Turns out I was
talking to a plant.

10:37.419 --> 10:38.507
- [giggle]

10:38.638 --> 10:40.291
- Blair!

10:40.422 --> 10:42.424
- Oh, maybe if we
go past those trees,

10:42.554 --> 10:43.730
we'll find more clues.

10:43.860 --> 10:45.949
- But, Sunny,
won't we get lost too?

10:46.080 --> 10:47.255
- Hmm...
[gasps]

10:47.385 --> 10:48.604
I've got it!

10:48.735 --> 10:50.214
Do you have any
of your hair chalks?

10:50.345 --> 10:51.694
- Do I?

10:51.825 --> 10:52.956
I never leave home
without them.

10:53.087 --> 10:54.784
Now, let's see.

10:54.915 --> 10:57.004
Uh, apple, a hair roller--

10:57.134 --> 10:58.875
mint!

10:59.006 --> 11:00.834
Ooh, I wondered
where I'd put that.

11:00.964 --> 11:03.271
Mmm.
Aha, chalk!

11:03.401 --> 11:05.055
Told you.
Never leave home without them.

11:05.186 --> 11:06.709
- Perfect.

11:06.840 --> 11:07.841
We can mark the trees as we go.

11:07.971 --> 11:09.756
That way,
we can follow the marks

11:09.886 --> 11:11.409
back to camp
and not get lost.

11:11.540 --> 11:12.889
- Got it and on it.

11:13.020 --> 11:14.499
An X to mark the spot.

11:14.630 --> 11:15.544
- Good job.

11:15.675 --> 11:17.546
Now let's find Blair.

11:17.677 --> 11:19.766
- I can do this.
I can do this.

11:19.896 --> 11:23.117
I hope this is
the way back to camp.

11:23.247 --> 11:25.293
♪

11:25.423 --> 11:28.426
Oh, it doesn't look
like the way back.

11:28.557 --> 11:31.212
But maybe it's
the scenic route?

11:31.342 --> 11:33.083
♪

11:33.214 --> 11:37.218
This looks familiar, I think.

11:37.348 --> 11:38.828
[gasps]

11:38.959 --> 11:41.439
I've definitely
seen this rock before.

11:41.570 --> 11:42.876
[groans]

11:43.006 --> 11:46.314
I'm just going in circles.

11:46.444 --> 11:48.359
Eww.

11:48.490 --> 11:51.536
More dirt. Oh. Ugh.

11:51.667 --> 11:52.973
[creaking]
[gasps]

11:53.103 --> 11:56.454
That does not sound good.

11:56.585 --> 11:58.108
Ah! Time to go!

11:58.239 --> 12:00.850
♪

12:00.981 --> 12:06.551
Oh,
I guess I'll go this way then.

12:06.682 --> 12:08.902
I miss Sunny and Rox.

12:09.032 --> 12:10.294
♪

12:10.425 --> 12:12.296
- Look! A clue!

12:12.427 --> 12:13.384
Size 5 shoe.

12:13.515 --> 12:15.212
Blair definitely came this way.

12:15.343 --> 12:18.085
- [sighs]
This is a lot of nature.

12:18.215 --> 12:20.565
- We'll never find her now.

12:20.696 --> 12:21.828
- Oh, we can't give up.

12:21.958 --> 12:23.917
We've gotta find her.

12:24.047 --> 12:25.614
Come on,
we can face any challenge.

12:25.745 --> 12:27.529
- Like this sort of challenge?

12:27.659 --> 12:29.400
♪

12:29.531 --> 12:30.924
- This is why
I never leave home

12:31.054 --> 12:33.361
without my scissors and comb.

12:33.491 --> 12:35.667
[grunting]

12:35.798 --> 12:38.235
This tree just needed
a little hairstyling.

12:38.366 --> 12:39.846
- Thanks, Sunny.

12:39.976 --> 12:41.325
Oh, can't forget
to mark this tree

12:41.456 --> 12:43.327
if we wanna
find our way back.

12:43.458 --> 12:45.721
♪

12:45.852 --> 12:47.767
- Look, a boat.

12:47.897 --> 12:50.160
- But the boat's on the
other side of the stream.

12:50.291 --> 12:52.423
That won't help us.

12:52.554 --> 12:55.557
- Blair must've used the boat
to get to the other side.

12:55.687 --> 12:57.211
- Great!

12:57.341 --> 12:59.430
Wait, then how do we
get to the other side?

12:59.561 --> 13:01.258
- We make a raft.

13:01.389 --> 13:03.086
Let's gather some branches.

13:03.217 --> 13:05.523
And I'll need some ribbon
from my accessory apron.

13:05.654 --> 13:08.178
[bright music]

13:08.309 --> 13:15.229
♪

13:15.359 --> 13:16.534
Ah.

13:16.665 --> 13:18.580
Practical and pretty.

13:18.710 --> 13:20.147
- And I found an oar!

13:20.277 --> 13:22.236
It's not a very good oar.

13:22.366 --> 13:24.281
What we need is a sail.

13:24.412 --> 13:26.457
- I don't think it'll make
a very good sail, either.

13:26.588 --> 13:27.502
- No problem.

13:27.632 --> 13:29.243
One hair cape coming up.

13:29.373 --> 13:31.811
- That is better than my stick.

13:31.941 --> 13:33.116
♪

13:33.247 --> 13:34.161
- Ugh!
- Oh.

13:34.291 --> 13:35.466
- Hoo.
- Phew.

13:35.597 --> 13:37.729
♪

13:37.860 --> 13:38.818
- Oh...

13:38.948 --> 13:41.690
[laughing]
- Yay!

13:41.821 --> 13:43.561
- I wish I could go back.

13:43.692 --> 13:46.129
Oh, if only I knew
which way   was  back.

13:48.871 --> 13:52.570
Oh, if only I wasn't all alone.

13:52.701 --> 13:54.137
[gasps]

13:54.268 --> 13:56.444
I guess I'm not all alone,
am I?

13:56.574 --> 13:57.706
[nervous laugh]

13:57.837 --> 13:59.055
[inhales deeply]

13:59.186 --> 14:01.623
Hi, I'm Blair.

14:01.753 --> 14:03.059
Oh, you're not so scary.

14:03.190 --> 14:05.801
In fact, you're kinda cute.

14:05.932 --> 14:09.196
I'm gonna call you
Boris the Bug.

14:09.326 --> 14:11.415
- We did it!
- Whoo-hoo!

14:11.546 --> 14:14.201
♪

14:14.331 --> 14:15.463
- X marks the spot.

14:15.593 --> 14:17.030
- Yes, it does.

14:18.553 --> 14:19.510
- [gasps]

14:19.641 --> 14:20.816
- Oh, no.

14:20.947 --> 14:21.948
- Now what?

14:22.078 --> 14:24.037
♪

14:24.167 --> 14:25.952
- We can't go around.

14:26.082 --> 14:27.910
We'll just have to go over.

14:28.041 --> 14:31.827
These super strong hair clips
will definitely come in handy.

14:31.958 --> 14:35.309
[grunts] Maybe we'll see
Blair from up top.

14:35.439 --> 14:37.354
- [grunts]

14:37.485 --> 14:38.138
- Blair?

14:38.268 --> 14:39.530
Blair!

14:39.661 --> 14:41.619
- Just a lot of trees.

14:41.750 --> 14:43.534
Wait, I see something!

14:43.665 --> 14:47.974
No, just more trees.

14:48.104 --> 14:50.367
- What goes up must come down.

14:50.498 --> 14:53.762
Super springy,
super strong hair elastics.

14:53.893 --> 14:55.372
Great for ponytails and...

14:55.503 --> 14:56.852
- Bungee!

14:56.983 --> 15:02.858
♪

15:02.989 --> 15:03.815
- We did it!

15:03.946 --> 15:05.513
- Wait, another X.

15:05.643 --> 15:08.733
♪

15:08.864 --> 15:12.128
- Ohh. Hmm.

15:12.259 --> 15:16.089
If we were Blair,
which path would we choose?

15:16.219 --> 15:17.917
- I bet she went this way.

15:18.047 --> 15:19.614
- Wow, how can you be so sure?

15:19.744 --> 15:23.096
- I'm guessing not many spiders
read "Manicure Monthly."

15:23.226 --> 15:26.664
- [giggling]
Great job, Rox.

15:26.795 --> 15:27.752
[distant rumbling]

15:27.883 --> 15:29.885
- [gasps]Oh, no.

15:30.016 --> 15:32.583
I think it's about to...
- Rain!

15:32.714 --> 15:39.808
♪

15:41.288 --> 15:44.291
[birds chirping]

15:47.207 --> 15:49.774
- Where are my
hair chalk markers?

15:49.905 --> 15:52.255
- The rain must have
washed them away.

15:52.386 --> 15:54.214
- Oh, no!
But that means...

15:54.344 --> 15:56.259
- We're lost too!

15:58.566 --> 16:00.655
- Let's split up
and look for clues.

16:00.785 --> 16:03.310
[curious music]

16:03.440 --> 16:05.312
♪

16:05.442 --> 16:06.443
Ah.

16:06.574 --> 16:08.010
both:
Oh!

16:08.141 --> 16:09.969
- Oops, sorry,
didn't see you there.

16:10.099 --> 16:11.318
- It's hopeless.

16:11.448 --> 16:12.928
We'll never find Blair.

16:13.059 --> 16:14.495
We'll never get home.

16:14.625 --> 16:16.801
And we'll never eat
marshmallows!

16:16.932 --> 16:18.716
- Never say never, Rox.
[distant singing]

16:18.847 --> 16:20.283
- Did you hear that?

16:20.414 --> 16:23.721
I know that singing anywhere!

16:23.852 --> 16:25.593
both:
Blair!

16:25.723 --> 16:27.421
- ♪ Like I do

16:27.551 --> 16:29.858
♪ You'll never wonder
where I'm gonna be ♪

16:29.989 --> 16:32.774
And a little dash of glitter.

16:32.904 --> 16:35.168
[giggling]
Perfect!

16:35.298 --> 16:38.127
These woods are almost
a home away from home.

16:38.258 --> 16:39.650
Almost.

16:39.781 --> 16:40.825
both:
Blair!

16:40.956 --> 16:43.524
- [gasps]
Sunny! Rox!

16:43.654 --> 16:45.308
[laughter]

16:45.439 --> 16:47.267
Oh, am I glad to see you!

16:47.397 --> 16:49.399
I saw a giant spider

16:49.530 --> 16:51.706
and got so scared I ran away.

16:51.836 --> 16:53.534
And then I got scared because
I couldn't find my way back.

16:53.664 --> 16:55.449
And then I realized
I was lost

16:55.579 --> 16:57.581
and I got even more scared.

16:57.712 --> 16:59.757
Someone should really put
some sign posts out there.

16:59.888 --> 17:01.063
Hey, wait a minute.

17:01.194 --> 17:03.065
You look just
like the giant spider!

17:03.196 --> 17:05.807
- There was no giant spider,
Blair.

17:05.937 --> 17:08.853
Just my hairstyle, see?

17:08.984 --> 17:11.073
I'm sorry I scared you.

17:11.204 --> 17:12.640
- Aw, it's okay, Rox.

17:12.770 --> 17:14.772
I'm not scared of bugs anymore.

17:14.903 --> 17:17.166
They made sure
I didn't get lonely.

17:17.297 --> 17:18.863
Bugs are really interesting

17:18.994 --> 17:21.214
when you're not
running away from them.

17:21.344 --> 17:23.172
Like, this insect
can walk upside down.

17:23.303 --> 17:25.827
And that one
can blend in with leaves,

17:25.957 --> 17:27.481
like he's invisible.

17:27.611 --> 17:30.875
Um, at least
I think he's still there.

17:31.006 --> 17:33.052
[giggle]
He's very good at it.

17:33.182 --> 17:38.013
♪

17:38.144 --> 17:39.797
I shouldn't have run off.

17:39.928 --> 17:42.017
Thanks for coming
and finding me.

17:42.148 --> 17:43.627
- We're just glad you're okay.

17:43.758 --> 17:45.847
But if you ever get lost again,

17:45.977 --> 17:47.109
just stay where you are.

17:47.240 --> 17:49.285
That way,
you'll be easier to find.

17:49.416 --> 17:51.461
- Speaking of being lost,

17:51.592 --> 17:53.637
all our chalk markers
washed away.

17:53.768 --> 17:56.858
How are we gonna
find our way back?

17:56.988 --> 17:58.903
- Oh, Blair, the compass!

17:59.034 --> 18:00.470
- The compass, right!

18:00.601 --> 18:01.819
[humming]

18:01.950 --> 18:03.038
Uh-oh.

18:03.169 --> 18:03.995
- What uh-oh?

18:04.126 --> 18:05.823
- Uh...

18:05.954 --> 18:06.824
I forgot it.

18:06.955 --> 18:08.217
- We're doomed!

18:08.348 --> 18:09.653
- It's okay.

18:09.784 --> 18:11.829
Maybe we can
make our own compass.

18:11.960 --> 18:14.441
Hm, let's see...

18:14.571 --> 18:16.182
I'm gonna need a leaf.

18:16.312 --> 18:18.836
Oh, this is perfect.

18:18.967 --> 18:20.490
Oh, and a bobby pin.

18:20.621 --> 18:22.013
Gotta rub it on her hair.

18:22.144 --> 18:23.711
- [grunting]

18:23.841 --> 18:25.278
Sunny, you know,

18:25.408 --> 18:28.107
I did say I was sorry
for running away.

18:28.237 --> 18:29.717
- No, no, no, look!

18:29.847 --> 18:31.762
When I rub the bobby pin
on your hair,

18:31.893 --> 18:33.721
it turns it into a magnet!

18:33.851 --> 18:37.116
And magnets point north,
just like my compass.

18:37.246 --> 18:39.161
That means this way is north,

18:39.292 --> 18:40.815
and that's the way
to our campsite.

18:40.945 --> 18:42.033
- And the marshmallows.

18:42.164 --> 18:43.513
Don't forget the marshmallows.

18:43.644 --> 18:44.645
[giggling]

18:44.775 --> 18:46.342
- Wait!

18:46.473 --> 18:48.518
It was nice to meet you, Boris.

18:48.649 --> 18:51.347
Don't eat too many
of those leaves, Eric.

18:51.478 --> 18:54.002
And thanks for keeping
me company, Sylvia.

18:54.133 --> 18:55.482
[sighs]

18:55.612 --> 18:57.527
Now I'm ready to go.

18:57.658 --> 19:00.400
[laughter]

19:00.530 --> 19:03.011
- Wow, Sunny,
your compass really worked!

19:03.142 --> 19:04.534
What an adventure.

19:04.665 --> 19:07.624
Oh, I am good
at camping after all.

19:07.755 --> 19:09.017
- Oh, no.

19:09.148 --> 19:10.975
Everything's been rained on.

19:11.106 --> 19:12.673
- [gasps]
The marshmallows!

19:12.803 --> 19:15.502
♪

19:15.632 --> 19:17.286
It's okay. They're okay.

19:17.417 --> 19:19.462
- I guess our camping
adventure is over.

19:19.593 --> 19:21.377
- Oh, but I just good at it!

19:21.508 --> 19:23.379
- We can come back
another day.

19:23.510 --> 19:25.120
Right now we should
get everything...

19:25.251 --> 19:26.556
[shuffling, zipping]
Packed up and tidied away--

19:26.687 --> 19:28.384
- Done! Ha!

19:28.515 --> 19:30.995
[both laughing]

19:31.126 --> 19:32.780
- No time to waste.

19:32.910 --> 19:34.782
We can have the marshmallows
back at the salon.

19:34.912 --> 19:36.175
[grunting]

19:36.305 --> 19:37.785
Next time, let's pack lighter.

19:37.915 --> 19:39.656
[both laughing]

19:39.787 --> 19:44.270
♪

19:44.400 --> 19:46.141
- And on our next camping trip,

19:46.272 --> 19:47.751
I'm going to take my tablet

19:47.882 --> 19:50.101
so I can draw
the new wildlife I find.

19:50.232 --> 19:51.886
- Even the bugs?

19:52.016 --> 19:52.843
[both laughing]

19:52.974 --> 19:54.497
- Especially the bugs!

19:54.628 --> 19:56.847
Did you know
Sylvia had so many legs

19:56.978 --> 19:58.632
I couldn't count them all!

19:58.762 --> 20:01.374
I'm glad she didn't
want her nails done.

20:01.504 --> 20:03.289
[giggling]

20:03.419 --> 20:05.987
- And all that nature inspired
a brand-new hairstyle.

20:06.117 --> 20:07.293
Ready to give it a try?

20:07.423 --> 20:08.859
- So ready!

20:08.990 --> 20:10.818
[both laughing]

20:10.948 --> 20:13.560
[bright music]

20:13.690 --> 20:15.301
- Okay.

20:15.431 --> 20:16.824
♪

20:16.954 --> 20:18.217
Oh, perfect.

20:18.347 --> 20:20.567
Well, what do you think?

20:20.697 --> 20:23.047
- I look like a spider too!

20:23.178 --> 20:25.746
Just like Rox and Boris.

20:25.876 --> 20:27.008
[giggling]

20:27.138 --> 20:28.444
I love it.

20:28.575 --> 20:30.011
It's too bad I don't
get to wear it

20:30.141 --> 20:32.187
in the great outdoors.

20:32.318 --> 20:34.189
- You can! Follow me!

20:34.320 --> 20:38.585
♪

20:38.715 --> 20:41.805
Welcome to your new campsite.

20:41.936 --> 20:44.417
We have everything the
modern camping girl could want,

20:44.547 --> 20:46.332
just a little closer to home.

20:46.462 --> 20:47.855
- [squealing]

20:47.985 --> 20:50.510
[excited giggling]

20:50.640 --> 20:52.207
[both laughing]

20:52.338 --> 20:53.817
- What are you waiting for?

20:53.948 --> 20:55.993
You're not scared of bugs,
are you?

20:56.124 --> 20:57.908
[both laughing]

20:58.039 --> 20:59.823
♪

20:59.954 --> 21:01.564
- I thought I heard voices.

21:01.695 --> 21:04.001
Sunny? Rox? Blair?

21:04.132 --> 21:05.916
Hello?

21:06.047 --> 21:07.222
Hey...
[sniffing]

21:07.353 --> 21:09.572
Where is everybody?

21:09.703 --> 21:13.010
[stammering]
Spiders!

21:13.141 --> 21:14.969
- It's okay, Doodle.

21:15.099 --> 21:16.710
It's just us.

21:16.840 --> 21:19.103
- Oh, and Sunny's brand-new
spider hairstyles.

21:19.234 --> 21:21.018
[giggling]
- Phew!

21:21.149 --> 21:24.021
Hey...
[sniffing]

21:24.152 --> 21:25.806
Is that marshmallow I smell?

21:25.936 --> 21:26.807
- Sure is.

21:26.937 --> 21:28.025
- Whoo-hoo!

21:28.156 --> 21:28.939
[together]
Whoa!

21:29.070 --> 21:30.463
- [munching]

21:30.593 --> 21:31.942
- Say "camping!"

21:32.073 --> 21:34.510
both:
Camping!

21:34.641 --> 21:37.296
- Definitely one
for the Style Files.

21:37.426 --> 21:40.473
[laughter]

21:42.213 --> 21:43.693
- Hi, it's me, Sunny.

21:43.824 --> 21:46.435
Wanna take a look
inside the Style Files?

21:46.566 --> 21:49.656
I love that wild spider style.

21:49.786 --> 21:51.092
Wow.

21:51.222 --> 21:53.050
For this hairstyle and more,

21:53.181 --> 21:56.184
check out Sunny's Style Files
at nickjr.com

21:56.315 --> 21:57.446
and the Nick Jr. app.

21:57.577 --> 22:00.667
Keep smiling, keep styling!
[laughs]

22:05.106 --> 22:07.978
[upbeat music]

22:08.109 --> 22:15.464
♪
